# This file explains cloning GitHub repo and trigerring Jenkins to build when a change is detected in GitHub repo.

1. Select the project to be used. In our case, it will be the python project we created in step 2.

2. Select "Git" under "Source Code Management" section.

3. Add the GitHub repo that you want to build.

4. Select "Build when a change is pushed to GitHub" under "Build Triggers". 

5. Go to your GitHub repo's settings.

6. Under "Webhooks and services" tab on left panel, go to "Services"

7. Click on "Add service" and search for "jenkins" in the drop down list.

8. Select "jenkins (GitHub plugin) and add Jenkins hook URL as http://jenkins_server_ip/github-webhook/

9. Click on "Add service" and this service will be added.
